|Bùi
|Vietnamese form of Pei, from Sino-Vietnamese ''裴 (bùi)''.
|-
|Buu
|A royal Vietnamese surname created by the Nguyễn Dynasty.
|-
|Đàm
|Vietnamese form of Tan, from Sino-Vietnamese 譚 ''(đàm)''.
|-
|Dang
|
|-
|Đào
|Vietnamese form of Tao, from Sino-Vietnamese 陶 ''(đào)''.
|-
|Đỗ
|Vietnamese form of Du, from Sino-Vietnamese ''杜 (đỗ)''.
|-
|Du
|From Chinese ''杜 (dù)'' meaning "stop, prevent" or "birchleaf pear tree".
|-
|Giang
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''江 (giang)'' meaning "river".
|-
|Hoa
|
|-
|Hoàng
|Vietnamese form of Huang, from Sino-Vietnamese ''黃 (hoàng)''.
|-
|Huang
|From Chinese ''黄 (huáng)'' meaning "yellow".
|-
|Lê
|Vietnamese form of Li, from Sino-Vietnamese ''黎 (lê)''.
|-
|Mai
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''梅 (mai)'' meaning "plum, apricot" (refers specifically to the species Prunus mume).
|-
|Nguyễn
|Vietnamese form of Ruan, from Sino-Vietnamese ''阮 (nguyễn)''. This is the most common Vietnamese surname, accounting for over a third of the population.
|-
|Phùng
|Vietnamese form of Feng, from Sino-Vietnamese 馮 ''(phùng)''.
|-
|Ta
|
|-
|Thái
|Vietnamese for Cai.
|-
|Thanh
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''青 (thanh)'' meaning "blue, green, young" or ''聲 (thanh)'' meaning "sound, voice, tone".
|-
|Tôn
|Vietnamese form of Sun.
|-
|Trần
|Vietnamese form of Chen, from Sino-Vietnamese ''陳 (trần)''.
|-
|Triệu
|Vietnamese form of Zhao, from Sino-Vietnamese 趙 ''(triệu)''.
|-
|Trịnh
|Vietnamese form of Zheng, from Sino-Vietnamese 鄭 ''(trịnh)''.
|-
|Võ
|Variant of Vũ, used more often in southern Vietnam.
